This paper proposes a new system design for information centric networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of caching and routing, which are topics related to distributed systems and data structures, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely categories as well. The paper also proposes a model to analyze the system, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses metrics such as load and time to find content, which are topics related to performance evaluation, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category as well.
